<div class="blog-left">

<h1>What is black hat SEO?</h1>

<p class="glossary-intro"><dfn>Black Hat SEO</dfn> is the use of dubious optimisation techniques in an attempt to manipulate the search engine's algorithms to rank a website or webpage higher in the search results.</p>

<h2>Examples of black hat SEO</h2>

<p>There are numerous tactics that dishonest digital marketers have employed over the years in an attempt to improve their search presence, a few of the more popular methods being:</p>

<ul>
 	<li>Buying or selling links</li>
 	<li>Spinning one piece of written content, such as a blog post, into many with slight word changes</li>
 	<li>Stuffing keywords into content</li>
 	<li>Hiding keywords on the page by making them the same colour as the background</li>
 	<li>Hiding keywords behind images</li>
 	<li>Stuffing keywords onto a 'doorway page' to attract the search engines attention but serving a more user-friendly page to the actual user</li>
 	<li>Getting a page to rank and switching it for spammy content</li>
 	<li>Copying part or the entirety of another website onto your own</li>
 	<li>Posting excessively in comments sections of external websites with links to your website</li>
 	<li>using or creating low quality websites with the sole purpose of linking to your main website</li>
 	<li>Using article writing machines (known as NLG or Natural Language Generators) to create content</li>
</ul>

<h2>Black hat techniques and the Google algorithm</h2>

<p>Black hat techniques were once very successful and most SEOs who have been in the game a long time will have at one point or other used techniques now deemed black hat. With several incremental advances in the Google algorithm, courtesy mainly of Panda and Penguin updates, black hat techniques either no longer work, are on the way out or have already been penalised.</p>

<h2>The advantages of black hat SEO</h2>

<p>While the SEOniverse would never in a million years suggest using any black hat tactics for your own short-term ranking gains, monitoring the successes an failures of other Black Hat sites has the advantage of giving insight into when the search engine algorithms change. http://www.blackhatworld.com/</p>

<p><a href="http://www.blackhatworld.com/">Black Hat World</a> is a digital marketing community marketplace  that's all about making money online using blac khat methods. Monitoring the forums here when the search engine algorithms are in flux can give you a fantastic idea of the types of black hat tactics that are being penalised and inform you if your site is at risk of a penalty.</p>

